ata Type (not specified).\n\nThe purpose of this interface is to configure and manage the properties of a database field within an application development environment.\n\n\n  \n  6: Editor help and tips  \n If available, this bar provides helpful tips and information related to the element currently open in the editor. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/80c52e08febca366bc999d68b547ed314825e5fb.png]\nDescription: The image contains a UI text element labeled \u0022Name,\u0022 describing it as the name of the model element. It states that the name is mainly used for providing model elements with a human-readable name. Additionally, it notes that in some cases, the name serves as an identifier of the model element, which is relevant for defining XML structures or for requesting constants from XSLT transformations. The content appears to be part of a documentation or help system related to a software development tool.\n\n\n  \n  7: Search bar  \n A standard full-text search bar that allows you to search across the entire model. \n   \n  8: Browser  \n The browser shows all the elements of your project model. The key section is the Model Browser, which is organized in a tree view with categories: Common, Data, Business Logic, and API. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/8e5cb4daea457b5a88ffa5c8ebf0578e0d43278e.png]\nDescription: The image displays a Model Browser interface, likely for a development or data management tool, organized in a hierarchical tree structure. The main sections are labeled as \u0022Common,\u0022 \u0022Data,\u0022 \u0022Functions,\u0022 \u0022Lookups,\u0022 \u0022Tree Structures,\u0022 \u0022User Interface,\u0022 \u0022Business Logic,\u0022 and \u0022API.\u0022 Under the \u0022Data\u0022 section, \u0022Constants,\u0022 \u0022Data Structures,\u0022 \u0022Database Data Types,\u0022 and \u0022Entities\u0022 are displayed, with \u0022Entities\u0022 further expanded to show \u0022myproject,\u0022 incorporating subcategories like \u0022Project,\u0022 \u0022Task,\u0022 \u0022Organization Management,\u0022 \u0022Partner Management,\u0022 \u0022Resource Management,\u0022 \u0022Root Menu,\u0022 \u0022Security,\u0022 \u0022Synchronization,\u0022 and \u0022Work Queue.\u0022 The apparent purpose is to navigate and manage components within a data model project.\n\n\n  \n  9: Browser tab bar  \n This is where you can switch between the various entities visible in the Browser, such as the Model Browser, Packages, Properties (for the currently open element in the editor), and the Results from search or other actions. \n   \n   The client application \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/c/c127b222fce6f687eac5bf648e72bf0fe8fbfd9d.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for an application called \u0022Origam.\u0022 At the top, the label \u0022ORIGAM\u0022 is prominently featured. Below, on the left side, the interface presents a vertical navigation menu with the following labels: \u0022Work Queue,\u0022 \u0022Favourites,\u0022 \u0022Menu,\u0022 \u0022Settings,\u0022 \u0022General,\u0022 \u0022Maps,\u0022 \u0022Users \u0026 Security,\u0022 with sub-items including \u0022Active Sessions,\u0022 \u0022Add User,\u0022 \u0022Application Roles,\u0022 \u0022My User Profile,\u0022 \u0022User Permissions...,\u0022 \u0022User Roles,\u0022 and \u0022Users.\u0022 At the bottom, there are additional items labelled \u0022Info\u0022 and \u0022Search (0).\u0022 The right side of the interface appears blank, likely intended for content display or interaction. The overall purpose of this interface seems to be user management or administrative tasks within the Origam application.\n\n\n  \n  1: Placeholder for logo or specific information  \n This section typically contains the logo of the system operator, but it can also display other information, such as a timer, stopwatch, or the name of the object the user is currently working with. For example, if I am processing a specific apartment within a building, I can display its name here. \n  2: Menu bar  \n The menu area typically includes user queues, a menu of individual modules, and system actions, along with options for my favorites, data items, and search results. ","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:35:23"},"vector":[-0.041791454,-0.007913766,-0.064290814,-0.017837608,-0.019035809,-0.054962363,0.016322223,0.0011280176,-0.012255177,-0.0044690953,0.011555353,-0.007727012,-0.030130383,0.018899761,-0.0012558223,0.007087057,0.021554235,0.008879894,0.017465392,0.022920283,-0.011642154,-0.016275166,-0.0034164458,0.023959082,-0.009800656,0.03341641,-0.010841026,-0.031285133,-0.0021329306,0.021391489,0.013465776,-0.058926906,0.0014263534,-0.005472393,-0.007887937,-0.009714201,0.013829829,0.011456667,-0.04957526,0.017493637,-0.008450601,0.013641329,-0.008031954,0.006076365,0.017454552,-0.04649219,-0.0047408384,-0.003197378,-0.010525957,-0.038264148,-0.036281664,-0.05453541,0.011417934,-0.036193885,0.013769065,0.017429741,-0.07051617,-0.019849597,-0.0821124,0.011089712,-0.034781866,-0.021167869,0.0013143197,-0.043171756,-0.004881019,0.01228396,-0.02882287,0.003278481,-0.025360934,-0.013982356,-0.0034723734,0.00869068,-0.06395149,-0.041097313,-0.053279057,0.024367062,-0.005348049,0.0077986154,-0.05880046,0.029173544,-0.0068389755,0.0149702085,-0.006167472,-0.021045713,0.028535724,0.019553676,-0.026984598,0.07622452,0.030776592,0.027513787,-0.058783084,-0.021650076,0.05608328,-0.045988005,-0.05191015,0.008367303,-0.01944292,-0.023685884,0.0030227848,0.009220247,-0.04620754,-0.017745424,-0.025261631,0.0016670964,-0.011725316,-0.018919485,0.015635578,-0.025833113,-0.014931114,-0.034088816,0.009835149,0.023182476,0.05147856,0.0026618934,0.011125542,-0.015014181,0.006121002,-0.022793354,-0.028209075,0.0139813805,-0.008072802,0.009456843,0.073492356,-0.00902929,-0.02